BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
[`[$eq[0]]`] is in standard form, with [`A=2.7\text{,}`] [`B=3.4\text{,}`] and [`C=-82\text{.}`]

[`[$eq[1]]`] is in point-slope form, with slope [`\frac{2}{7}\text{,}`] and passing through [`\left(3,\frac{1}{10}\right)\text{.}`]

[`[$eq[2]]`] is linear, but not in any of the forms we have studied. Using algebra, you can rearrange it to read [`y=12x-5\text{.}`]

[`[$eq[3]]`] is not linear. The exponent on [`x`] is a dead giveaway.

[`[$eq[4]]`] is in standard form, with [`A=1\text{,}`] [`B=-1\text{,}`] and [`C=10\text{.}`]

[`[$eq[5]]`] is in slope-intercept form, with slope [`4`] and [`y`]-intercept at [`(0,1)\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

